title: Apollo Astronaut Walter Cunningham Dies at 90
summary: Former astronaut Walter Cunningham, who flew into space on Apollo 7, the first flight with crew in NASA’s Apollo Program, died early Tuesday morning in Houston. He was 90 years old.

title: SpaceX launches 114 small satellites on first mission of 2023
summary: SpaceX’s first launch of the year hauled 114 small satellites into polar orbit for operators in 23 countries. Liftoff occurred at 9:56 a.m. EST (1456 GMT) Tuesday. The first stage of the Falcon 9 rocket returned to Cape Canaveral for landing about eight-and-a-half minutes later.

title: NASA Awards Space and Earth Sciences Data Analysis-V Contract
summary: NASA has awarded the Space and Earth Sciences Data Analysis-V (SESDA-V) contract to ADNET Systems, Inc. of Bethesda, Maryland, to provide Earth and Space Science research and development at the agency’s Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland.

title: SpaceX kicks off 2023 with second largest rideshare launch
summary: After rounding out 2022 with the world’s last orbital launch, SpaceX has kicked off 2023 with the new year’s first orbital launch...

title: Space Force launches weather-imaging cubesat for year-long demonstration
summary: The U.S. Space Systems Command on Jan. 3 launched a cubesat intended to demonstrate commercial weather imaging technologies for military use.

title: Iridium enters service agreement for direct-to-smartphone satellite service
summary: Iridium has entered into a service provider agreement with a company widely expected to be Samsung to connect its satellites to smartphones.

title: SpaceX begins 2023 with Transporter-6 launch
summary: After a record-setting year of launch activity in 2022, SpaceX kicked off the new year Jan. 3 with a Falcon 9 launch of more than 110 smallsats.

title: After doubling launch record in 2022, can SpaceX take another step up in 2023?
summary: The company may aim for as many as 100 launches in 2023.

title: NASA planetary science budget remains under stress
summary: Despite a small funding increase for 2023, NASA’s planetary science programs still face “significant stress” financially that contributed to the delay of one mission and could push back the start of others.

title: SpaceX rings in 2023 with Transporter-6 rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX began another busy year with the launch of the Transporter-6 rideshare mission from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station (CCSFS). The mission lifted off at 9:56 AM EST (14:56 UTC) on Tuesday, Jan. 3, 2023. Falcon 9’s first stage returned to land at Landing Zone-1 at CCSFS approximately eight and a half minutes after launch.
